The paper proposes a new learnable similarity measure for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and evaluates its effectiveness in visual recognition and few-shot learning tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the regularization of the similarity measure, which suggests a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL) where regularization techniques are commonly used.
